description:
Service Usage

The service is used to store an information record and its associated metadata into the Record Keeping System (currently implemented via TRIM) for an indefinite period of time. When storing an information record the user has the capability to specify whether the information record can be further modified (eg functionality of Drafting Correspondence) or whether it is to be locked down as a final version.
readme:
Service Usage

The service is used to store an information record and its associated metadata into the Record Keeping System (currently implemented via TRIM) for an indefinite period of time. When storing an information record the user has the capability to specify whether the information record can be further modified (eg functionality of Drafting Correspondence) or whether it is to be locked down as a final version.
The execution of this service is a step that is likely to occur when a consumer wishes to store metadata and Information Record (IR)
This service allows the consumer to store/relate a single information record into multiple business context containers and multiple parties containers. The consumers provides at least one Business Context and optionally parties with the Information Record to be stored. The Information Record is physically stored only within a single Business Context Container and related to other Business Context and party containers.
An Information Record could be a single document or a correspondence with a list of attachments.

Service Behaviour

This service provides information record storage in the following steps:
The consumer provides the following metadata and Information Record inputs:
Binary Large Objects (for storing electronic copies) and related
Metadata
Metadata only if hard copy information records
Related Information Record ID and relationship type
Record Management Access Groups
Record Management Security Classification and Caveats
Business Contexts
Party Contexts
Electronic Container ID.
The service invokes Create/Search Container, Store Document and Link Document Record Keeping Services (RKS) passing the metadata and the Information Record.
RKS executes the service call and returns either:
A Record ID for the newly stored Information Record
A Record ID of the container where the Information Record is contained in.
A Paper File Created Flag for the Business Context container that the IR is contained in.
Business Context (with Business Context Container Id)
Client Sub Container Context (with Client Subcontainer Id)
OR
An Enterprise Error detailing why the service was unsuccessful.
A consumer of this service receives either:
A Record ID for the successfully stored information record
An Electronic Container ID
A paper File Created Flag
An optional list of Business Context
An optional list of Party Context
OR
An error message if an information record cannot be stored successfully for technical reasons
This service has been altered to use MTOM/XOP by changing the base64Binary fields to xsd:anyType so that a reference to the attachment can be sent. This is converted by ESB to a base64Binary attachment reference before it is sent to RKS. The developer can choose to either convert the link into a base64 or not convert and not validate.

Service Variants

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique identifier for Business Context as a Business Context Id with Business Context Type and Sub Type and a valid Electronic Container ID. This service also expects that the Meta information provided with a document will be record keeping compliant.

Service Composition

Although this service is not a composite service i.e. it is not composed of other enterprise services within the Service Portfolio, it makes a call to SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 in order to retrieve details available for a selected Parties in a consolidated records. These party details are used by the provider service to search and create party containers and party sub containers

Service Flow

The normal flow for this service is a call to RMS to store information record. The return message contains TRIM unique Record Id.
The following service flow describes a successful execution path.
Service Invocation and Retrieve Multiple Parties
Service Consumer invokes service SV059 on ESB with StoreInformationRecordRequest.
Use AF1 IF StoreInformationRecordRequest.InformationRecord.StoreiNformationRecord.StoreCorrespondence.PrimaryCorrespondenceItem.BodyContentRenditionList!=NULL
AND StoreInformationRecordRequest.InformationRecord.StoreiNformationRecord.StoreCorrespondence.PrimaryCorrespondenceItem.BodyContent= NULL.
IF PartyContext is provided with the service request, ESB transforms StoreInformationRecordRequest into RetrieveMultiplePartiesRequest with the Party Ids from those Party Contexts for which the PartyContext.PartySubContainerId=NULL.
ESB invokes SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 with RetrieveMultiplePartiesRequest.
ESB receives RetrieveMultiplePartiesResponse from SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0.
Use AF2 if SV002.1 Retrieve Multiple Parties v02.0 fails.
Store and Process the Record into Business Context Container
ESB transforms StoreInformationRecordRequest and RetrieveMultiplePartiesResponse into StoreRecordRequest.
ESB invokes RecordKeeping.storeRecord () with StoreRecordRequest.
ESB receives response StoreRecordResponse from RecordKeeping.StoreRecord ().
Use AF3 if RecordKeeping.StoreRecord () fails.
ESB transform StoreRecordResponse into StoreInformationRecordResponse.
ESB return StoreInformationRecordResponse to service consumer.
Alternate Flow 1
ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E05 to consumer.
Alternate Flow 2
If SV002.1 times out, ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E03 to consumer else ESB capture the error code and error message from SV002.1 and concatenate to body of message SV059.MSG-E01 then return to consumer
Alternate Flow 3
If StoreRecord is timeout, ESB returns message SV059.MSG-E03 to consumer else ESB capture the error code and error message from RecordKeeping.storeDocumentSet() and concatenate to body of message SV059.MSG-E01 then return to consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No State management required.
